    "lesson_content_markdown": "# The Matrix Capstone: Final Defense\n\nYou have survived the journey through the Time Matrix. From the simple past to the sophisticated causative and participle clauses of the academy, you are now ready for the **Final Defense**.\n\n### 1. The Strategy: Synthesis\nIn a professional research report, you do not use only one tense. You synthesize multiple structures to show logic and cause.\n\n- **Sequence**: Use **Past Perfect** to show what happened first.\n- **Brevity**: Use **Participle Clauses** to save space in your abstract.\n- **Objectivity**: Use **Impersonal Passives** to sound objective and scientific.\n- **Delegation**: Use **Causatives** to show who was responsible for the tasks.\n\n### 2. Final Checklist\n- Did you use the **Base Form** (V1) for have/make causatives?\n- Did you use **been + V3** for perfect passives?\n- Did you use **Having + V3** for completed participle clauses?\n- Are your life experiences in the **Present Perfect**?\n\nTake your time. This is the final step to earning your **Gold Medal** in the Time Matrix.\n\n---",
